<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870303-0133 </DOCNO><HL> Combustion Engineering Job</HL><DD> 03/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CSP FREST </IN><DATELINE> STAMFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Combustion Engineering Inc. said it received a $50 million contract from China to provide equipment and design services for a 600,000-kilowatt coal-fired power plant.    A state-owned utility will build the plant at a generating facility in Ningbo, about 100 miles south of Shanghai. Combustion Engineering, a supplier of technical services and equipment to utilities and processing plants, said delivery of equipment is scheduled to begin in early 1988. Commercial operation is expected to start in 1990. </TEXT></DOC>